One folk cure thing that has completely disappeared culturally is wet clothes. People used to take cold baths at a spring with their shirt, then put on thick clothes over it and wear it all day. People put wet night caps on babies. They cured colds by going to sleep in wet socks.

The only cultural mention of such practices I recall was Ron Swanson character in that sitcom saying he was never hungover because when he got drunk he put on a pair of wet socks and went to bed that way. I guess it's just a blood circulation thing
